# Caddy Reverse Proxy Environment Variables
#
# ⚠️  NOT NEEDED for internal CA (local_certs) - This is the default setup
#
# This file is ONLY required if you switch to Let's Encrypt with DNS-01 challenge
# For internal CA: No .env file needed, Caddy generates certificates automatically

# ============================================================================
# Let's Encrypt Configuration (OPTIONAL)
# ============================================================================
# To use Let's Encrypt instead of internal CA:
# 1. Remove 'local_certs' from Caddyfile global options
# 2. Uncomment DNS provider variables below
# 3. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 4. Add to docker-compose.yml: env_file: .env
# 5. Restart Caddy: docker compose down && docker compose up -d

# Cloudflare
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your_cloudflare_api_token_here

# Namecheap
# NAMECHEAP_API_USER=your_namecheap_username
# NAMECHEAP_API_KEY=your_namecheap_api_key

# Other providers: https://caddyserver.com/docs/automatic-https#dns-challenge
